-- Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Interconexion Electrica, Aval
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-17T21:26:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-interconexion-electrica-aval.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 1.6 percent to 13,291.73, while the
Colcap Index gained 1.3 percent to 1,597.95.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil producer,
gained 1.9 percent to 4,500 pesos. The company said yesterday
there were no “significant” production cuts because of a labor
protest.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (PFAVAL CB), Colombia’s
biggest banking group by assets, gained 0.8 percent to 1,205
pesos. The company will hold bond investor meetings from Jan. 19
to Jan. 24, according to a person familiar with the plan.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and JPMorgan Chase & Co. are
arranging the meetings, said the person, who asked not to be
identified in accordance with company policy.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , Latin America’s
biggest power-line operator, rose 0.4 percent to 10,980 pesos.
The company plans to bid for energy-transmission projects in
 Chile  this year, Portafolio newspaper said, citing an interview
with Chief Executive Officer Luis Fernando Alarcon yesterday.  ISA, as the Medellin-based company is known, also plans to
bid for projects in Peru and Brazil, Alarcon told the Bogota-
based daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
